ull, "body": "Hello Rust developers,\r\n\r\nMy project is a binary project:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Cargo.lock\r\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Cargo.toml\r\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 src\r\n \u00a0\u00a0 \u251c\u2500\u2500 a.rs\r\n \u00a0\u00a0 \u251c\u2500\u2500 main.rs\r\n \u00a0\u00a0 \u2514\u2500\u2500 z.rs\r\n```\r\n\r\nWithout `edition = \"2018\"`, my imports work:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nmod a;\r\nmod z;\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith `edition = \"2018\"`, above imports don't work. Prefixing `crate::a` or `self::a` doesn't work either.\r\n\r\nError message is:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nerror[E0658]: imports can only refer to extern crate names passed with `--extern` on stable channel (see issue #53130)\r\n  --> src/main.rs:13:5\r\n   |\r\n1  | mod a;\r\n   | ------ not an extern crate passed with `--extern`\r\n```\r\n\r\nI stripped down the error message at line `#13`, it's just `use a::something;`.\r\n\r\nI think it's a bug, may I ask if you could verify?\r\n\r\nThank you,", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/57252/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/57252/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed"}